        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic vitreous-retinal disease characterized by ocular developmental anomalies such as microcornea a shallow anterior chamber glaucoma and cataract. Abnormal chorioretinal pigmentation is present usually lying between the vortex veins and the ora serrata for 360 degrees."
